[[File:MobquetA-1Deluxe.jpg|thumb|right|250px|The RS-J24 thruster engines visible on the sides of the Mobquet A-1 Deluxe Floater.]]The '''RS-J24 thruster engine''' was a cheap-yet-reliable [[Engine/Legends|engine]] module utilized by the [[Mobquet Swoops and Speeders/Legends|Mobquet]] [[A-1 Deluxe Floater/Legends|A-1 Deluxe Floater]]. The six engines, though hardy and compact, were fitted on the outside of the craft and only offered the A-1 Deluxe a top speed of 160 kph; this left each individual engine max speed at approximately 27 kph. The engines also ran very hot, and relied on cooling shrouds to protect passengers while entering and exiting the A-1.

